<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E45FFB790BF9D980579F836" bold="true" box="[199,315,2007,2033]" pageId="8" pageNumber="472">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DB8357C59E45FFB7913E9D980605F836" authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[326,583,2007,2033]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="8" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E45FFB7913E9D980605F836" box="[326,583,2007,2033]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="472">Ololaelaps caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from former Soviet Union (
<bibRefCitation id="781251B79E45FFB794399D9801D6F835" author="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V." box="[1089,1428,2007,2034]" pageId="8" pageNumber="472" pagination="61 - 87" refId="ref8032" refString="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V. (1964) Mites of the genus Ololaelaps Berlese, 1964 (Acarina: Laelaptidae). Parazitologicheskii Sbornik, 22, 61 - 87. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1964">Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964</bibRefCitation>
) where it was found from oleaster thickets and litter under ash tree in 
<collectingCountry id="64946CD69E44FFB693DB9AD907ACFF77" box="[931,1006,150,176]" name="Russia" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Russia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="64946CD69E44FFB6945C9AD900CBFF77" box="[1060,1161,150,176]" name="Armenia" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, respectively. 
<bibRefCitation id="781251B79E44FFB695519AD8052CFF12" author="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V." pageId="9" pageNumber="473" pagination="61 - 87" refId="ref8032" refString="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V. (1964) Mites of the genus Ololaelaps Berlese, 1964 (Acarina: Laelaptidae). Parazitologicheskii Sbornik, 22, 61 - 87. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1964">Bregetova &amp; Koroleva (1964)</bibRefCitation>
had designated 
<typeStatus id="C33892E49E44FFB6925C9AF406C4FF12" box="[548,646,187,213]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">syntypes</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName id="DB8357C59E44FFB692CE9AF40711FF13" authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[694,851,187,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB692CE9AF40688FF12" box="[694,714,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB692A09AF40711FF13" box="[728,851,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in this study, a 
<typeStatus id="C33892E49E44FFB694749AF50031FF13" box="[1036,1139,186,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">lectotype</typeStatus>
is chosen from among the examined 
<typeStatus id="C33892E49E44FFB691739A900533FF3E" box="[267,369,223,249]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">syntypes</typeStatus>
. The 
<typeStatus id="C33892E49E44FFB691D59A910656FF3F" box="[429,532,222,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">lectotype</typeStatus>
is necessary to stabilise the distinction between 
<taxonomicName id="DB8357C59E44FFB694499A90008CFF3F" authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[1073,1230,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB694499A900007FF3E" box="[1073,1093,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB6942B9A90008CFF3F" box="[1107,1230,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other species discussed here. The species has never been recorded again after its original description. We herein provide the following additional morphological information to complement the original description of 
<bibRefCitation id="781251B79E44FFB694E39B6804A0FEA2" author="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V." pageId="9" pageNumber="473" pagination="61 - 87" refId="ref8032" refString="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V. (1964) Mites of the genus Ololaelaps Berlese, 1964 (Acarina: Laelaptidae). Parazitologicheskii Sbornik, 22, 61 - 87. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1964">Bregetova &amp; Koroleva (1964)</bibRefCitation>
by examining type series specimens, all these observations were made on all 
<specimenCount id="0A85E7CF9E44FFB694359B0500B7FEA3" box="[1101,1269,330,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" type="generic">five specimens</specimenCount>
examined, unless specified: (1) dorsal shield essentially smooth, without reticulation (i.e. not reticulate, but completely micropunctate) over whole surface except ventrolateral margins (epipleura) which are relatively well extended ventrally and with lineate-reticulate ornamentation, cells narrow and oriented mostly longitudinally or diagonally (
<figureCitation id="84B830C39E44FFB695479BF904F4FE33" captionStart="FIGURES 26–30" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 26–30. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps caucasicus Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 26, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 27, sternal shield; 28, subcapitulum; 29, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 30, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571762/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Figs 26, 29</figureCitation>
), length of dorsal setae decreasing from anterior to posterior, in 
<specimenCount id="0A85E7CF9E44FFB693E89B940069FE33" box="[912,1067,474,501]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
a supernumerary seta 
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB695529B940101FE33" box="[1322,1347,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Jx</emphasis>
present between 
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB690869BB00548FDDF" box="[254,266,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">J</emphasis>
-series (this feature is difficult to discern in the other 
<specimenCount id="0A85E7CF9E44FFB6930C9BB10063FDDF" box="[884,1057,510,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
due to bad conditions of slides); (2) metasternal setae 
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB691F2986D05E9FDFB" box="[394,427,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">st4</emphasis>
and metasternal poroids located on soft cuticle in 
<specimenCount id="0A85E7CF9E44FFB69395986C00CAFDFB" box="[1005,1160,546,573]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
examined (
<figureCitation id="84B830C39E44FFB69576986D0121FDFB" box="[1294,1379,546,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–30" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 26–30. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps caucasicus Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 26, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 27, sternal shield; 28, subcapitulum; 29, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 30, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571762/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
), but this feature is difficult to discern in the other 
<specimenCount id="0A85E7CF9E44FFB692E99809077EFDA7" box="[657,828,582,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
due to bad condition of slides; (3) posterior margin of sternal shield straight (
<figureCitation id="84B830C39E44FFB691E298250662FD43" box="[410,544,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–30" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 26–30. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps caucasicus Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 26, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 27, sternal shield; 28, subcapitulum; 29, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 30, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571762/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Figs 26, 27</figureCitation>
); (4) metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, shield ornamented by transversally elongated cells and bearing five pairs of pre-anal setae (
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB693B198C1004EFD6F" box="[969,1036,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Jv1–3</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB6946398C10022FD6F" box="[1051,1120,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Zv1–2</emphasis>
) in addition to 
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB6956898C00172FD6E" box="[1296,1328,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">st5</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="84B830C39E44FFB6953898C104F5FD0B" captionStart="FIGURES 26–30" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 26–30. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps caucasicus Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 26, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 27, sternal shield; 28, subcapitulum; 29, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 30, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571762/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Figs 26, 29</figureCitation>
); (5) hypostomal groove with six transverse rows of denticles, each row with 4–7 relatively large denticles, groove wider anteriorly, progressively narrowing from anterior to posterior (
<figureCitation id="84B830C39E44FFB693819899000DFD37" box="[1017,1103,726,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–30" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 26–30. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps caucasicus Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 26, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 27, sternal shield; 28, subcapitulum; 29, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 30, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571762/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
); (6) the pretarsal paradactyli on legs II–IV not elongated, with tips not reaching beyond claws (
<figureCitation id="84B830C39E44FFB6930498B50792FCD3" box="[892,976,762,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–30" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 26–30. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps caucasicus Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 26, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 27, sternal shield; 28, subcapitulum; 29, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 30, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571762/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
); (7) insemination structures not discernible. Supplementary measurements (n=2): (1) lengths of dorsal setae decreasing from anterior to posterior, most of podonotal setae 55–64 and opisthonotal setae 25–45; (2) sternal shield length 113–115, maximum width 200–229, between coxae II 113–117; (3) hologastric shield 357–408 long (4) sternal setae (
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB6945099290035FC47" box="[1064,1143,870,897]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">st1–st4</emphasis>
) 55–59, metasternal setae 
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB690EF99C404FAFC62" box="[151,184,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">st5</emphasis>
and pre-anal setae (
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB691E199C505A2FC63" box="[409,480,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">JV1–3</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB6919699C5067BFC63" box="[494,569,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">ZV1–2</emphasis>
) 52–58; (5) legs: II (356–375), III (380–388) I and IV (470–500). 
<taxonomicName id="DB8357C59E44FFB6955999C50550FC0F" authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB6955999C50550FC0F" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Ololaelaps caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DB8357C59E44FFB6921299E00748FC0F" authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[618,778,943,969]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB6921299E0063CFC0E" box="[618,638,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2EF7F0549E44FFB692F699E00748FC0F" box="[654,778,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is distniguished mostly by the larger number of deutosternal denticles, longer dorsal setae and the narrower (compressed) cells of the epipleura (compare 
<figureCitation id="84B830C39E44FFB6957A999D013FFC2B" box="[1282,1405,978,1004]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–30" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[159,1429,181,1697]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 26–30. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps caucasicus Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 26, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 27, sternal shield; 28, subcapitulum; 29, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 30, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571762/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Figs 26, 29</figureCitation>
vs 
<figureCitation id="84B830C39E44FFB690EF99B9055AFBD6" box="[151,280,1014,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–47" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@12.[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 43–47. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps ussuriensis Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 43, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 44, sternal shield; 45, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 46, subcapitulum; 47, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571772/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Figs 43, 45</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
